headline: Why Estée Lauder (EL) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of beauty products company Estée Lauder (NYSE:EL) jumped 3.8% in the afternoon session after the stock rebounded amid a broader market rally as Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell hinted at potential interest rate cuts. The broad market optimism, which saw the Dow Jones Industrial Average surge over 700 points, overshadowed Estée Lauder's own recent negative news. Just the day before, the company reported a net loss of $1.13 billion for fiscal 2025, marking its third straight year of fall
